This is the Perl distribution Class-Accessor-Bundle.

INSTALLATION

Class-Accessor-Bundle installation is straightforward. If your CPAN shell is
set up, you should just be able to do

    % cpan Class::Accessor::Bundle

Download it, unpack it, then build it as per the usual:

    % perl Makefile.PL
    % make && make test

Then install it:

    % make install

DOCUMENTATION

Class-Accessor-Bundle documentation is available as in POD. So you can do:

    % perldoc Class::Accessor::Bundle

to read the documentation online with your favorite pager.

